<span class="displaytext">arlington, va -- (candidate last)-palin 2008 today announced that richard petty, widely known as the greatest driver in nascar history, is endorsing (candidate full) for president. petty is announcing his endorsement at today's bank of america 500 at lowe's motor speedway in charlotte, n.c. <p>"what we need right now in these uncertain times is a steady hand on the wheel -- a leader we can trust to put country first, ahead of politics," petty said. "(candidate full) has always done that, and if you need proof, think about the sacrifices he made for america. i don't think there is any question that (candidate full) is a proud american and he has done more to better america than anyone. </p><p>"(candidate full) has a plan to get our economy back on track not only for the folks here in north carolina but also nationwide. he understands that higher taxes will only make things worse and he'll support small businesses and create jobs. he will get us on the road to energy independence and give our troops what they need to succeed in iraq and afghanistan. i'm proud to support (candidate full) for president." </p><p>petty won 200 races during his career, a nascar record, and won a record seven winston cup championships. he won the daytona 500 seven times, also a record, and won 27 races in 1967 alone. </p><p>other participants in the (candidate last)-palin events at lowe's motor speedway include cindy (candidate last), former louisiana gov. buddy roemer, country music star cowboy troy and doug (candidate last), son of (candidate full). team owners jack roush and joe gibbs will serve as mrs. (candidate last)'s hosts, with roush accompanying her to the drivers' meeting and gibbs joining her for a tour of the garage area.</p></span>



